Title: An Act to Establish the Municipal Shoreline Protection Legal Fund
Official Title: An Act to Establish the Municipal Shoreline Protection Legal Fund
Number of Sections: 1
Source: versions - Documents and Disposition
Media Type: application/pdf
Strikethrough Detection: 2 sections found

================================================================================

Section 1:
132nd MAINE LEGISLATURE
FIRST SPECIAL SESSION-2025
Legislative Document No. 1904
S.P. 745 In Senate, May 6, 2025
Reference to the Committee on Environment and Natural Resources suggested and ordered
printed.
DAREK M. GRANT
Secretary of the Senate
Presented by Senator NANGLE of Cumberland.
Printed on recycled paper
1 Be it enacted by the People of the State of Maine as follows:
2 Sec. 1. 5 MRSA §3112 is enacted to read:
3 §3112. Municipal Shoreline Protection Legal Fund
4 1. Fund established. The Municipal Shoreline Protection Legal Fund, referred to in
5 this section as "the fund," is established in the office to assist municipalities in paying legal
6 costs incurred in pursuing egregious shoreland zoning violations.
7 2. Funding. The fund consists of money received from any public or private source.
8 The fund must be held separate and apart from all other money, funds and accounts.
9 Interest earned by the fund must be credited to the fund. Any unexpended balances
10 remaining in the fund at the end of any fiscal year do not lapse and must be carried forward
11 to the next fiscal year.
12 3. Administration. The office shall administer the fund. In accordance with rules
13 adopted by the office, the office shall provide money from the fund to a municipality to
14 cover legal costs incurred by the municipality in pursuing shoreland zoning violations the
15 municipality determines to be egregious.
16 4. Reimbursement. A municipality receiving financial assistance from the fund shall
17 reimburse the fund within 6 months of the settlement or final adjudication of the legal claim
18 for which the funding was received.
19 5. Fund balance. For each fiscal year, the Governor shall submit a funding level
20 recommendation for the fund that maintains a minimum balance in the fund of $100,000.
21 The recommendation must be transmitted to the Legislature within the time schedules in
22 section 1666.
23 6. Rules. The department shall adopt routine technical rules as defined in chapter 375,
24 subchapter 2-A to carry out the purposes of the fund.
25 Sec. 2. Appropriations and allocations. The following appropriations and
26 allocations are made.
27 EXECUTIVE DEPARTMENT
28 Municipal Shoreline Protection Legal Fund N528
29 Initiative: Provides one-time funding to establish the Municipal Shoreline Protection Legal
30 Fund.
31 GENERAL FUND 2025-26 2026-27
32 All Other $100,000 $0
33 __________ __________
34 GENERAL FUND TOTAL $100,000 $0
35
31 SUMMARY
3362 This bill establishes the Municipal Shoreline Protection Legal Fund in the Office of
3373 Policy Innovation and the Future to assist municipalities in paying legal costs incurred in
3384 pursuing egregious shoreland zoning violations. Municipalities are required to reimburse
3395 the fund within 6 months of the settlement or final adjudication of the legal claim for which
4306 the funding was received.
